Difference between sleep and wait
----------------------------------

Sleep()
-------
* Sleep is a static method present in Thread class

* sleep has 2 overloaded methods 
 1. sleep(long ms )
 2. sleep(long ms ,int nanos)


* it has a time limit

* it will does not release the lock during synchronization

* 



wait()
-------
* wait is non-static method present in object class

* it has 3 overloaded methods

 1. wait();
 2. wait(long ms);
 3. wait(long ms,int nanos);
* wait will wait until it will notified by notify() or notifyAll()

* it will release the lock during synchronization

*